Note:
==============================================================================
CURVE_P521 - NIST P-521 short Weierstrass curve operations (FIPS 186-4 D.1.2.5)
==============================================================================

Implements the NIST P-521 elliptic curve over Fp521:

    y^2 = x^3 + a*x + b  (mod p)
    a = -3
    p = 2^521 - 1  (Mersenne prime)

The base point G has order n with cofactor h = 1.

Wire format on the SEC 1 v2.0 layout uses 66-byte field elements (521 bits
left-padded with seven zero bits). Uncompressed points are 133 bytes
(0x04 || X(66) || Y(66)); compressed points are 67 bytes.

Coordinate system, scalar-multiplication ladder, encoding rules, and
arena discipline are identical to curve_p256.runa.

References:
- NIST FIPS 186-4 Appendix D.1.2.5 (curve P-521 parameters).
- SEC 1: Elliptic Curve Cryptography v2.0.
- SEC 2 v2.0 section 2.6.1 (secp521r1).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint.runa" as BigInt
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint_extra.runa" as BigIntX
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/field_p521.runa" as Field

Constant CURVE_P521_BYTES as Integer is 66
Constant CURVE_P521_LIMBS as Integer is 9
Constant CURVE_P521_POINT_BYTES as Integer is 133
Constant CURVE_P521_COMPRESSED_BYTES as Integer is 67
Constant CURVE_P521_JACOBIAN_STRUCT_BYTES as Integer is 24

Process called "curve_p521_b" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns b per FIPS 186-4 D.1.2.5.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate 20-limb BigInt and populate nine little-endian limbs.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single allocation. Public constant.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public curve parameter.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let b be proc bigint_alloc from BigInt with arena, 20
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 0, 17241221745651760896
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 1, 3851667882566759665
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 2, 1608559935907544839
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 3, 6204052985702421371
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 4, 13309414057048082913
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 5, 11734817516813489651
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 6, 10563792850091589870
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 7, 10754236788854528543
    proc bigint_set_limb from BigInt with b, 8, 81
    proc bigint_set_limb_count from BigInt with b, 9
    Return b
End Process

