Process called "curve_p521_point_alloc" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates a Jacobian point struct holding three BigInt pointers.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Allocate 24-byte struct + three 20-limb BigInts via field_p521_zero.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Four arena allocations.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No side-channel.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let pt be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, CURVE_P521_JACOBIAN_STRUCT_BYTES
    If pt is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let x be proc field_p521_zero from Field with arena
    If x is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let y be proc field_p521_zero from Field with arena
    If y is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let z be proc field_p521_zero from Field with arena
    If z is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with pt, 0, x
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with pt, 8, y
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with pt, 16, z
    Return pt
End Process

Process called "curve_p521_point_x" takes pt as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the X-coordinate BigInt pointer.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single load at offset 0.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Constant time.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Pure accessor.
    @End Security_Scope

    Return proc memory_get_qword from Memory with pt, 0
End Process

